This product uses the Citation Style Language — https://citationstyles.org/ —
and preserves the author/contributor metadata inside each .csl file.

To add journal styles, drop the corresponding `<style>.csl` files into this
directory (e.g. `nature.csl`, `apa.csl`, `vancouver.csl`, `ieee.csl`,
`american-chemical-society.csl`). They are baked into the binary via
`include_dir!` (see modules/citations/csl.rs) and listed by
`GET /api/citations/styles`. With no `.csl` here, the formatter falls back to
pandoc's built-in default (Chicago author-date), which requires no bundled file.
